    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-07-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="416" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Judge <persName type="from">Buckles</persName> to
                                Governor <persName type="to">Markham</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">En
                                        Route to Detroit</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-07-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">July
                                        28, 1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your letter of July 25, which was handed me at Suisun last
                            night as I passed en route to Detroit. I am aware that the district
                            attorney of Solano County has been putting forth every effort at his
                            command to bring the guilty parties in the Vallejo trouble to justice,
                            and I have referred your letter to him, with a request that he furnish
                            your excellency with a statement of the trouble and what his efforts
                            have been. Knowing the efficiency of police officers of my court and the
                            zeal of the district attorney to bring offenders to justice, I assure
                            you no effort will be spared to this end.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. J. Buckles</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Judge, Fairfield, Solano County,
                                Cal</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
